# Default-deny allowlist.
#
# Ignore every top-level entry, then explicitly un-ignore what we track.
# New stuff apps dump into ~/.config stays ignored until added below,
# so nothing leaks into the dotfiles repo by accident.
#
# `/*` is anchored to the repo root, so it only hides top-level entries —
# files *inside* an un-ignored dir are not re-ignored by it.
# To track a new dir/file: add a `!/<name>` line (keep alphabetical).
/*

# Files
!/.env.example
!/.gitignore
!/CONTEXT.md
!/README.md

# Directories
!/agents/
!/claude/
!/docs/
!/dwm/
!/git/
!/kitty/
!/nvim/
!/pi/
!/picom/
!/rofi/
!/scripts/
!/X11/
!/xdg-desktop-portal/
!/zed/
!/zsh/
